About Airwallex

Airwallex is a technology company that revolutionises the way businesses operate globally. Our financial infrastructure provides a modern technology stack for businesses to operate internationally, without the challenges of the current global financial system.

Businesses use Airwallex as their end-to-end global financial services platform. Whether it’s making or receiving payments from customers, domestically or internationally, Airwallex saves businesses time and money by offering real-time, reliable and cost-effective financial solutions. Our web and API solutions support businesses of all sizes, from small companies to large enterprises.

In this fast-changing digital world that is increasingly becoming borderless, our mission is to empower businesses of all sizes to grow in their own markets and around the world, and by doing so, contribute to the global economy.

Alternate bio focused on investors/funding

Founded in 2015, Airwallex has since grown to over 400 employees across ten offices around the world. Airwallex has raised over US$360 million in venture capital funding, supported by top-tier investors including Tencent, Sequoia Capital China, DST Global, Hillhouse Capital, Horizons Ventures, ANZi Ventures, Square Peg Capital, Mastercard and Salesforce Ventures.In March 2019, Airwallex was valued over US$1 billion after its Series C financing, and became one of the fintech unicorns in APAC. The company was also named one of the world’s top 50 fintechs in KPMG’s 2019 and 2018 Fintech100 lists.

Job Responsibilities:

1. Manage multi-cloud environments such as AWS and Alibaba Cloud through automated scripts, and deploy, maintain, and optimize the operating environment of cross-border payment products;
2. Manage database system, including access control and authorization, performance monitoring, tuning, problem diagnosis, data backup and recovery, etc .;
3. Through software and hardware monitoring to ensure the stable operation of various services, solve problems and hidden dangers;

4. Deploy and manage development test environment, improve existing tools and processes, and continuously improve development efficiency;

Qualifications:

1. Bachelor degree or above, major in computer and related majors; more than two years of experience in operation and maintenance of large-scale Internet websites, management of high concurrent volume system;
2. Have CI / CD implementation experience, familiar with Linux, common open source software, monitoring software and container technology, familiar with computer network;
3. Familiar with at least one language such as Shell, Python, Java, etc., with certain programming skills;
4. Strong ability to analyze and solve problems independently;
5. Have at least one database operation and maintenance management experience;
6. Have good English reading and writing skills;

Bonus:
Familiar with Cassandra / PostgreSQL / Redis / NoSQL;
Familiarity with Kubernetes
Familiar with ELK / Beats;
Familiar with software and hardware maintenance such as servers, firewalls, routers and switches;
Fluent in English.
